{"id":"24b47f2b-508d-4c8b-8762-81eb03710f0f","revision":0,"last_node_id":29,"last_link_id":110,"nodes":[{"id":1,"type":"MarkdownNote","pos":[-430,30],"size":[400,690],"flags":{},"order":0,"mode":0,"inputs":[],"outputs":[],"properties":{},"widgets_values":["## Usage\n\nLoad Your **Image** and **Models**\n\nIn the **LoRA Loader**, **enable** and set up Your **LoRA**s if any (first number column is **Model Strenght**, second is **Clip**). Tip: **Click** the **Arrow** buttons for **fine** adjustments, **CTRL** + **Click** for **bigger** steps. Click the **Number** to **Reset**.\n\nUse the **Prompt Library** to load Your **preset** or write **Prompt** and **Negative** prompt\n\nAdjust **Guider**, **Sampler**, **Scheduler**\n\nIf You **don't** want to upscale the **Image**, use the **Set Mode** nodes to **bypass** both **Upscale Image (using Model)** and **Upscale Image** nodes.\n\nIf Your **Upscale Model** is let's say **4x** but You only want **2x**, You can Resize **after** Upscaling: Make sure **both** Upscale Image (using Model) and Upscale Image nodes set to **Enabled**. Set the **Resolution Calulator**'s **Multiplier** to **2** which will take the **Input Image Dimensions**, multiplies it by **2** and passes it to the Upscale Image **Width** and **Height** parammeters.\n\nFinally, set the self-explanatory parameters of the **Tiled Sampler** and **run** the **Workflow**.\n\n---\n\n## Important!\n\n---\n\nDo **NOT** use **Mute** on Upscaler / Resizer! Enable or Bypass only.\n\n---\n\nThe **Multiplier** is applied to the **original** Input Image dimensions. With **Multiplier** set to **2**, You'll double the original image size regardless of what Upscale Model You're using if Resizer is enabled. When the Resizer is Bypassed, the Multiplier does nothing.\n\n---\n\n## Dependency\n\n---\n\nThis workflow uses **RMBG** to remove background, and since **RMBG**'s segmenter is **broken** (for me at least), **SAM3** is also required. Install those first. Alternatively, You can create and use Your own Mask(s).\n\n---\n\n## Black Output\n\n---\n\nYou may or may not get a black output. This is the result of some internal state corruption most likely coming from SAM3. Usually this issue is fixed by swapping checkpoint, running the workflow then swapping back to the ogiginal checkpoint. This only needs to be done once (per Comfy restart)."],"color":"#432","bgcolor":"#653"},{"id":3,"type":"LoadImage","pos":[0,190],"size":[400,480],"flags":{},"order":1,"mode":0,"inputs":[{"localized_name":"image","name":"image","type":"COMBO","widget":{"name":"image"},"link":null},{"localized_name":"choose file to upload","name":"upload","type":"IMAGEUPLOAD","widget":{"name":"upload"},"link":null}],"outputs":[{"label":"Image","localized_name":"IMAGE","name":"IMAGE","type":"IMAGE","links":[46,98]},{"label":"Mask","localized_name":"MASK","name":"MASK","type":"MASK","links":null}],"properties":{"Node name for S&R":"LoadImage"},"widgets_values":["Image.png","image"]},{"id":4,"type":"JohnsLoRALoader","pos":[430,30],"size":[500,640],"flags":{"collapsed":false},"order":4,"mode":0,"inputs":[{"localized_name":"Model","name":"Model","type":"MODEL","link":3},{"localized_name":"Clip","name":"Clip","type":"CLIP","link":4},{"localized_name":"JohnsLoRALoaderContainer","name":"JohnsLoRALoaderContainer","type":"STRING","widget":{"name":"JohnsLoRALoaderContainer"},"link":null}],"outputs":[{"localized_name":"Model","name":"Model","type":"MODEL","links":[52]},{"localized_name":"Clip","name":"Clip","type":"CLIP","links":[6]}],"properties":{"Node name for S&R":"JohnsLoRALoader","JohnsLoRALoaderContainer":"[]","JohnsLoRALoaderState":{"v":1,"folders":{"Flux.1 D":false,"Flux.1 Kontext":false,"Pony":true,"Qwen":false,"SD 1.5":true,"SDXL 1.0":true,"WAN":false},"loras":{"Flux.1 D\\Close Set Fakest Breasts.safetensors":{"en":false,"sm":1,"sc":1},"Flux.1 D\\Dark Nipples.safetensors":{"en":false,"sm":1,"sc":1},"Flux.1 D\\Fixed Nipples.safetensors":{"en":false,"sm":1,"sc":1},"Flux.1 D\\Ghost 